The paper focuses on user errors while performing security-critical tasks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it examines the impact of distractions on user behavior. The use of unexpected sounds as distractions also relates to the field of signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the development of a novel experimental setup, which could be relevant to the category of software engineering (cs.SE) or cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the study involves analyzing data and drawing conclusions, which could fall under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SD).
